- Describe the differences between forks, clones, and branches.  When would you
	use one instead of another?
- A fork is a copy of the repo on GH servers, I can use it for collaborative coding 
	or working from different devices, a clone is a local copy of the repo, to be used when 
	working locally or before pushing, while a branch is a parallel history of commits,
	where I can test experimental or different function I don't want the master to have

